HEADWORD: Jews-ears
<hw>Jew's"-ears`</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A widely distributed species of
edible fungus (<spn>Auricularia auricula-judae</spn>, formerly
<spn>Hirneola Auricula-Jud⟦ae⟧</spn>, or <spn>Hirneola Auricula</spn>),
bearing some resemblance to the human ear and growing on decaying
wood.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ear fungus, .</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

